                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-01-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Fletcher reports that the British minister and he to-day urged the President
                    of the foreign office to ratify the Chinchow agreement and to admit of the
                    participation of Japan and other interested powers, and that the President
                    replied that the general principles of the Chinchow project were approved by the
                    Chinese Government, but that China is inclined to await the result of the
                    changes now taking place before proceeding any further with the Chinchow
                    project</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
